subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Dorsal membranous process of paramere with papillae and bristles apically (
Fig. 6B
); fore wing with second cubital cell (2Cu) enclosed by spectral veins (
Fig. 4B
).

Head.
Antenna filiform, articulated to prominent and contiguous processes, apically thin, ratio of antennomeres: 13:3:9:10:9:8:8:7:7:9 (
Fig. 4A
); antennal toruli far from basal margin of clypeus; head shiny, smooth, unsculptured, covered with short setae, with dorsal side swollen (
Fig. 4D
); face with two visible incomplete longitudinal and median sutures, sutures only visible in basal half of region from clypeus to antennal toruli (
Fig. 4C
); frons without tracks of median furrow (
Figs 4C, 4E
); occipital carina complete (
Fig. 4E
); ocelli distinct; POL: 2, OL: 2, OOL: 3, OPL: 2, TL: 5; eye large, approximately 0.5 × head (
Fig. 4E
).

Mesosoma
.

Pronotum short, rugose, not visible in dorsal view, covered with short setae, hidden between head and anteromesoscutum, pronotum much shorter than half of mesoscutum (
Fig. 4F
); notaulus absent and parapsidal signum present (
Fig. 4F
); anteromesoscutum and mesoscutellum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, finely covered with short setae, with the track of median longitudinal striae in the apical third (
Fig. 4F
); mesoscuto-mesoscutellar suture deep and continuous (
Fig. 4F
); metanotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured (
Fig. 4G
); mesopleuron and lateral area of metapectal-propodeal complex shiny, weakly granulate, meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete (
Fig. 4I
); metapectal-propodeal complex smooth, shiny, unsculptured (
Fig. 4G
).

Colour.
Head brown (
Figs 4C–4E
), with mandible testaceous (
Fig. 4C
); antenna brown with second antennomere testaceous (
Fig. 4A
); mesosoma brown (
Fig. 4I
); metasoma and legs brown-testaceous (
Fig. 4J
).

